From e58da8135853dc668d3cc4df39d120efff427fa6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 23:33:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] odb: rename odb_source_type to odb_storage_format and add
 dispatch

Rename `odb_source_type` to `odb_storage_format` and move the enum
from `odb/source.h` to `repository.h`, mirroring how
`ref_storage_format` lives in `repository.h`.

Rename enum values: `ODB_SOURCE_UNKNOWN` becomes
`ODB_STORAGE_FORMAT_UNKNOWN`, `ODB_SOURCE_FILES` becomes
`ODB_STORAGE_FORMAT_FILES`. All existing users are updated.

Introduce a dispatch table `odb_backends[]` in `odb/source.c`,
indexed by `odb_storage_format`, mirroring how `refs_backends[]`
in `refs.c` maps `ref_storage_format` to ref backend constructors.

`odb_source_new()` now consults `repo->odb_storage_format` to select
the backend constructor from the table, falling back to the files
backend when the format is unknown.

In `setup.c`, add support for the `extensions.objectStorage` config
key, parsed the same way as `extensions.refStorage`. The
`repository_format` struct gains an `odb_storage_format` field,
initialized to `ODB_STORAGE_FORMAT_FILES` by default.

The ODB storage format is set on the repository struct before
calling `setup_git_env()`, so that `odb_source_new()` can select
the correct backend when creating the object database.

Add `odb_source_files_new_base()` wrapper that returns the base
`odb_source` pointer, for use in the dispatch table.

Extend the unit tests to cover the new format lookup functions,
`odb_source_init()`, `odb_source_release()`, and the NULL safety of
`odb_source_free()`.

Signed-off-by: Aaron Willoughby <aaron@omniband.org>
